org.hkijena.jipipe.api.algorithm

Class JIPipeIteratingAlgorithm

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hkijena.jipipe.api.algorithm.JIPipeGraphNode
      • org.hkijena.jipipe.api.algorithm.JIPipeAlgorithm
        • org.hkijena.jipipe.api.algorithm.JIPipeParameterSlotAlgorithm
          • org.hkijena.jipipe.api.algorithm.JIPipeIteratingAlgorithm
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JIPipeParallelizedAlgorithm, JIPipeValidatable, JIPipeParameterCollection
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ImageRoiProcessorAlgorithm, IteratingPythonScriptAlgorithm, MacroWrapperAlgorithm, MergeChannelsAlgorithm, ReferencedAppendRectangularRoiAlgorithm, ReferencedDefineRectangularRoiAlgorithm, RemoveBorderRoisAlgorithm, RoiToMaskAlgorithm, RoiToRGBAlgorithm

    public abstract class JIPipeIteratingAlgorithm
extends JIPipeParameterSlotAlgorithm
implements JIPipeParallelizedAlgorithm
    An JIPipeAlgorithm that iterates through each data row. This algorithm utilizes the JIPipeDataBatch class to iterate through input data sets. It offers various parameters that control how data sets are matched. If your algorithm only has one input and will never have more than one input slot, we recommend using JIPipeSimpleIteratingAlgorithm instead that comes without the additional data set matching strategies
